<TITLE> Warrants out on 'melamine milk' sellers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 18 (bdnews24.com) - Two cases were lodged and arrest warrants issued by a Dhaka court on Tuesday against importers and sellers of Chinese-made 'melamine-tainted' milk. Dhaka chief metropolitan magistrate Abdul Majid issued arrest warrants against owners of Mou Enterprise of Chittagong and Allway Trading of Dhaka for breach of the 1984 alternative to breast milk ordinance, by selling Sweet Baby brand, and for importing Yashli-1 and Yashli-2 brands without registration. The cases were lodged at the CMM court by Dr Fatema Parvin, director of the Public Health Nutrition Institute. Arrest warrants were issued after the court heard the charges. Advocate Abdul Mannan represented the plaintiff putting four witnesses on the stand. Witnesses included Shariful Islam, deputy director of BSTI, Dr Md Abdur Rahman, deputy director of the Public Health and Nutrition Institute, Emdad Abdul Majid, deputy director of the Ministry of Health and Family Planning and Hossain Malik of the Consumer Association of Bangladesh (CAB). bdnews24
